        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> My friends and I often enjoy playing in the Arena during guild parties.  We do 1 on 1's and team vs team.  Always fun.</P><P>However, as a necromancer, I am given a handicap every battle.  My friends insist that I mem NO DOTS.  NONE!  And we all know how limiting THAT is.  Without our dots, Necromancers become a low nuking wizards with a pet.  </P><P>Why do my friends insist on this?  Because when battling a Necromancer, there is a very high possibility my opponents will die from "pain and suffering."  And we all know what happens then: EXP LOSS.  Talk about being a downer at a party!</P><P>Now I'm not a programmer, and I know nothing about the code that goes into this game, but it seems to me that this would be a very very simple problem to correct.  When in "duel mode" or upon entering a "p vs p area", can't some 1 be changed to a 0 so that exp loss is impossible?  </P><P>Come on... if someone dies in an arena battle because I landed Splurt on them, they don't die of "pain and suffering."  They have died by my blood, sweat, and mana.  Though I could understand it might be difficult for the code to decide and announce that "Sytox has defeated Tankalot in battle" -- exp loss should be completely out of the question.</P><P>Sytox<BR>51 Heretic</P><P> </font></td>

