        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Exp loss during duels is caused from the death blow not being attributed to a PC.</P><P>Grav flux, Pet death, Charms are known ways that this happens.</P><P>I seen DoTs cause exp loss in two ways</P><P>1) DoTs often can cause the target to "bleed to death", This causes Exp loss. </P><P>2) If the caster of the DoTs dies before the target dies from the dots, this also can (not always and I cant figure out way)cause exp loss</P><P>If the target dies directly from a tick of DoT damage then no exp is lost.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
